{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566687","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566687"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:46:46+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:46:46+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18867"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18867","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18867"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.23,0.16,0.21,0.15,0.25]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11600"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92800"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11600","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11600"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18867"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"76159"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11322"},{"type":"tags","id":"11323"},{"type":"tags","id":"11324"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27306"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27310"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92800","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/92800"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA medical practitioner with five years of clinical experience takes a 24-month break from clinical practice to pursue research. They maintain their medical registration during this period but do not engage in any clinical work. They now wish to return to full-time clinical practice.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the requirements this practitioner must meet before returning to clinical practice?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Complete one year of continuing professional development activities","Undertake a formal clinical assessment","No additional requirements are needed","Submit a professional development plan for board approval","Complete six months of supervised practice"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct requirement is to \u003Cstrong\u003Ecomplete one year of continuing professional development activities\u003C/strong\u003E. According to the Medical Board\u0027s recency of practice requirements, practitioners who have not engaged in clinical practice for between 12 and 36 months must complete the equivalent of one year\u0027s CPD activities relevant to their intended scope of practice before returning to practice. These CPD activities should be designed to maintain and update the practitioner\u0027s knowledge, clinical judgment, and professional skills.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENo additional requirements are needed\u003C/strong\u003E - This only applies to breaks of up to 12 months\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESubmit a professional development plan for board approval\u003C/strong\u003E - This is only required for breaks longer than 36 months\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EComplete six months of supervised practice\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Eundertaking formal clinical assessment\u003C/strong\u003E- These are both not standard requirements under recency of practice regulations however completing supervised practice or undertaking clinical assessments could form part of the professional development plan for doctors who have taken a break for longer than 36 months.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Medical practitioners returning to clinical practice after 12-36 months break must complete one year\u0027s equivalent of continuing professional development activities before recommencing practice.","The recency of practice requirements apply regardless of the reason for the break from clinical practice (research, parental leave, illness, etc).","CPD activities must be relevant to the intended scope of practice and maintain knowledge and clinical judgment."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx.","AHPRA and National Boards. Information on returning to practice [online]. 2023 [Cited 2025 Jan 16]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/Codes-Guidelines-Policies/FAQ/FAQ-Recency-of-practice.aspx."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"76159"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18867"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"76159","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/76159"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-19T13:20:22+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-19T13:20:30+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11600"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92800"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitabl